description: {"blocks":[{"key":"92svg","text":"We provide a detailed protocol to isolate and culture primary cortical neurons from the cortex of mice at embryonic day 15.5. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"2k870","text":"This protocol is designed to generate primary cultures of cortical neurons from the cortex of E15.5 mice.  The protocol is designed based on the dissection of brain tissues from 4 embryos, but it can be scaled up as needed.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1pda","text":"The protocol is structured in two sections:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ctrgl","text":"1. Tissue Dissection","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ahi44","text":"2. Culture plating and maintenance","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1m8mj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8r6vs","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a67k2","text":"The length of the protocol is ~9 days  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b370c","text":"Please Note: Breeding and euthanasia of all animal work should be performed in accordance with an institutionally approved animal care and use protocol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"d630f","text":"Collect the embryos in a 10 cm Petri dish with ice-cold HBSS-G and cut the heads.  Keep the Petri dish on ice while dissecting. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"erb6d","text":"Using a microscope, insert the tip of tweezers into the eyes to keep the head fixed, cut up from the cranial floor to the nose, open the skull like a book, and lift the cortices with tweezers. Using a clean 10cm Petri dish with ice-cold HBSS-G for each 3-4 embryos reduces excessive contamination with blood.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"48p1s","text":"Dissect the cortex by removing hindbrain and olfactory bulbs, and trim away meninges. Use tweezers to lift the meninges without puncturing the cortex tissue.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7pjqn","text":"Transfer the cortex to the 15ml tube containing 14ml of HBSS-G on ice. 4 heads per 15mL tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"47l04","text":"After dissections are complete, work inside the biosafety cabinet. Aspirate the HBSS-G, leaving as little of the dissection medium as possible without disturbing the tissue or exposing it to air. Add ~5ml/tube of warm HBSS-G/trypsin. Incubate for 20 minutes at 37C in a water bath. Invert the tube\u2028 every 5 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8si7p","text":"Meanwhile, dilute the DNAse I 1:10 in warm trypsin-inhibitor solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"avk4a","text":"Remove the tube containing trypsin and pieces of tissue from the water bath. \u2028Spray it with 70% ethanol and wipe it down before moving it into the hood. Aspirate trypsin solution and add ~5ml warm HBSS-G. Let the pieces of tissue settle to the bottom of the tube for 1-2 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7f084","text":"Aspirate HBSS-G, leaving as little of the dissection medium as possible without disturbing the tissue or exposing it to air. Add 1ml NB/trypsin-inhibitor/DNAse I. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dacjd","text":"Spin cells for 5 minutes at 1200 rpm at RT. Resuspend the pellet in warm culture medium (NBC). If a blood ring is present in the cell pellet, avoid carrying over the blood. Use a total volume of ~ 1ml/embryo. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d18l5","text":"Plate the cells in desired culture dishes. Use ~50% of final volume of NBC for initial plating. Incubate at 37 in the incubator for 5 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3607a","text":"Aspirate the initial culture media and replace it with fresh warm NBC (final volume). This step helps the removal of floating dead cells and debris. For example, for a 10 cm dish, use 10ml as final volume.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"51n9u","text":"Change 50% of culture media every 3 days. Add AraC at a final concentration of 4uM starting from day 3. Cultures are maintained until DIV 9. We noticed that after DIV9 the viability is reduced. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fdgls","text":"Triturate tissue pipetting up and down using a 1ml tip. Avoid introducing bubbles. Using the fewest strokes possible to dissociate the tissue is important to improve cell survival. Triturating over 15 times seems to reduce neuron survival. Let any chunk of non-dissociated tissue sink at the bottom of the tube for 1-2 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4co2q","text":"Transfer dissociated neurons to a new 50ml tube with a nested 40um mesh pre-rinsed with NBC (~2-3mL) and leave the chunks at the bottom. After transferring neurons, do a post-rinse of the 40um mesh with NBC.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
